    Frequently Asked Questions

    What is the median home price in Las Vegas?
    Homes for sale in Las Vegas have a median listing price of $325K. Some of these homes are Hot Homes, meaning they're likely to sell quickly.
    How long do homes stay on the market in Las Vegas?
    Most homes for sale in Las Vegas stay on the market for 48 days and receive 2 offers. In the past month, 6670 homes have been sold in Las Vegas. The median price per square foot in Las Vegas has increased by 5.5% over the past year.
    What are some of the most popular neighborhoods in Las Vegas?
    Popular neighborhoods include Sun City Summerlin, Centennial Hills, Southeast Las Vegas, South Las Vegas, Summerlin, Southwest Las Vegas, Summerlin Centre, Red Rock, Summerlin West, Downtown Las Vegas, The Lakes, Desert Shores, Northwest Las Vegas, Skye Canyon, and Lone Mountain.
    How often does Redfin update their new listings?
    Redfin is refreshed with the  newest listings in Las Vegas every 15 minutes.

    In the past month, 2381 homes have been sold in Las Vegas. In addition to houses in Las Vegas, there were also 2226 condos, 772 townhouses, and 111 multi-family units for sale in Las Vegas last month.
